                                    &#160;</div></ulink></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para><graphic fileref="images/fieldset.1.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/></para><para>Instead of e.g. inputting one name in an author field and another name in a translator field, here you choose the "roles" played by each "named entity" with regard to the publication. Most frequently used are, of course, author and editor, but it is possibile to record many specialised roles.</para><para>Also, it is possible here to have one person or one institution play different roles with regard to the same publication: the same person may e.g. have both edited and translated a certain work. To attribute more than one role to one and the same name, you click the '+' button under the Role label.</para><para>In most cases, drop-down lists like those illustrated above will have default values, here "author" in Role, but this value you can of course change as you wish. You do not have to set the value to blank if you do not use the field(s) it relates to, here the name fields.</para></chapter></book>